Level 1: Basic Retrieval
	a) Find an actor and all movies they acted in that were released before a date.
	b) 
Level 2: Relationships & Filtering
	a) Co-occurrence: Find Co-Actors.
	b) Multi-Role: List individuals who both acted in and directed the same movie.
	c) Exclusive Filtering: Find all people who have directed a movie but have never acted in any movie.
Level 3: Aggregation & Logic
	Top Performers: Return the top 5 actors who have appeared in the highest number of movies, including their movie count.
	Collaborators: For a specific actor (e.g., "Tom Hanks"), find their most frequent collaborators (actors they've worked with more than once).
	Graph Breadth: Find all people within two degrees of separation from "Keanu Reeves" (exclude Keanu himself).
Level 4: Complex Paths & Cleanup
	Shortest Path: Find the shortest path of relationships between "Tom Cruise" and "Hugo Weaving."
	Refactoring: Write a query to find a movie titled "The Matrix," change its tagline property to "Welcome to the Real World," and return the updated node.